<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.3/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css">
  <title>REST API</title>
</head>

<body>
  <div class="container">
    <h1 class="text-center my-4">Welcome to REST API Homepage</h1>
    <p class="lead">This is the homepage of the REST API. This api is using EJS templating with expressjs. Here a
      product list with fruits and vegetables is displayed. The data is stored in a data.js file which is not persitent.
      As soon as you create a new product, it will be added to the list. However, as you refresh the page, it
      added item will be removed from the list. This is a full fledged CRUD API. I have followed the conventional API
      pattern to develop this REST API. These patterns are as shown below:</p>
    <table class="table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>HTTP Verb</th>
          <th>HTTP Method</th>
          <th>Description</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>GET</td>
          <td>/products</td>
          <td>Get all products</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>GET</td>
          <td>/products/:id</td>
          <td>Get a single product</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>POST</td>
          <td>/products</td>
          <td>Create a new product</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>PUT</td>
          <td>/products/:id</td>
          <td>Update a product</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>DELETE</td>
          <td>/products/:id</td>
          <td>Delete a product</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <hr>
    <img class="img-fluid w-100" src="https://picsum.photos/700" alt="random">
    <a class="btn btn-success mt-3 d-flex mx-auto w-25 justify-content-center" href="/products">Go to products</a>
  </div>

</body>

</html>